SIMPLE: scaphite
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Scaphite
<hw>Scaph"ite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>scapha</ets> a boat, fr. Gr. <grk>ska`fh</grk> a boat, anything dug
or scooped out, fr. <grk>ska`ptein</grk> to dig.]</ety>
<fld>(Paleon.)</fld> <def>Any fossil cephalopod shell of the genus
<gen>Scaphites</gen>, belonging to the Ammonite family and having a
chambered boat-shaped shell. Scaphites are found in the Cretaceous
formation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Scaphocephalic</ent>⟦br⟧
